Sentencas: Nano-scale LSM-YSZ composite electrodes are prepared from a mixture of yttria stabilized zirconia (YSZ) and strontium-doped lanthanum manganite (LSM) particles.
Titulo: Effect of starting particulate materials on microstructure and cathodic performance of nanoporous LSM-YSZ composite cathodes

Sentencas: Commercial YSZ particles are mixed with polymerizable complex method-driven LSM powders of two different particle sizes, namely, 81 and 210nm.
Titulo: Effect of starting particulate materials on microstructure and cathodic performance of nanoporous LSM-YSZ composite cathodes

Sentencas: Then, the correlations between the properties of the starting particles, sintering temperature, microstructure and cell performance are studied.
Titulo: Effect of starting particulate materials on microstructure and cathodic performance of nanoporous LSM-YSZ composite cathodes

Sentencas: Use of smaller LSM particles in the composite electrode induces extensive grain growth.
Titulo: Effect of starting particulate materials on microstructure and cathodic performance of nanoporous LSM-YSZ composite cathodes

Sentencas: This significantly reduces the triple phase boundary (TPB) and leads to an increase in the polarization resistance.
Titulo: Effect of starting particulate materials on microstructure and cathodic performance of nanoporous LSM-YSZ composite cathodes

Sentencas: The composite cathode derived from larger LSM articles exhibits a lower total polarization resistance (similar to 0.31 Omega cm(2) at 800 degrees C) and, subsequently, better maximum cell power (similar to 630 mA cm(-2)).
Titulo: Effect of starting particulate materials on microstructure and cathodic performance of nanoporous LSM-YSZ composite cathodes

Sentencas: By contrast, larger resistance and lower cell power are observed for electrodes composed of smaller LSM particles.
Titulo: Effect of starting particulate materials on microstructure and cathodic performance of nanoporous LSM-YSZ composite cathodes
